Speaker 1: And your zip code, Mr. Scruggs?

Speaker 2: 90740.

Speaker 1: 90740, give me just a sec. Scott. All right, you've got it.

Speaker 2: All right, Scott, it looks like you got the 10 pills of the new Viagra AGV.

Speaker 1: Did you want to just do that same order again, or do you want to get more or less? Or not less, but more?

Speaker 2: Yeah, not less.

Speaker 1: Can you refresh my memory on how much they are?

Speaker 2: You got 10 pills for $63.95.

Speaker 1: If you were at 25 pills, which is just the next quantity up, it'd be $113.95. $50 more.

Speaker 2: Yeah, and do you have any military—

Speaker 1: Pricing or discounts? Unfortunately, not. Currently, we definitely do appreciate that service, though.

Speaker 2: Okay. All right, I always ask. You never know.

Speaker 2: Is it normal to just take one pill or two pills?

Speaker 1: You got a 50 milligram option, so it's just up to you, really.

Speaker 2: Some people, I mean, the doctor doesn't want anyone taking more than a 100—

Speaker 1: But they say you can take one or two. Some people split them in half, too, you know.

Speaker 2: So it's just really how much you need. Everybody's bioavailability is a little different.

Speaker 1: So when you say split them in half, you could even take less than one?

Speaker 2: I mean, if it works, yeah. It just depends how much you need, you know. If 25 milligrams works, that's perfect.

Speaker 1: Some people, they want the 50 milligram, they get the 100, and they just split them in half, you know, twice as many.

Speaker 2: Oh, I got you. All right, let's go with the second quantity that you mentioned.

Speaker 1: And then you're at 4181 Ironwood Avenue, Seal Beach, 90740?

Speaker 2: Yeah, and it's shipped discreetly, right?

Speaker 1: It is, yeah, absolutely. Just your name will be on it.

Speaker 2: And then, Scott, I have your Discover card here that ends at 2747. Is that the card you wanted to use?

Speaker 1: Yeah, that works.

Speaker 2: All right, give me just a sec.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right, you're all set, Mr. Scruggs. Your order's been placed.
